The union of sovereignty and liberty was well maintained for nearly 100 years by his suc- cessors ; and this first part of the Antonine age, as it is called, was the happiest and best period of the empire. The hereditary principle was in abeyance for the time ; Nerva adopted Trajan; and Hadrian, Antoninus Pius, and M. Aurelius came in turn to the throne by adoption.
